        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 6:24PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hartsel, or 64 miles southwest of Denver, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hartsel.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
